@@TJvCustomStaticText
Summary
  TJvCustomStaticText is the base class for TJvStaticText.
Description
  TJvCustomStaticText is the base class for TJvStaticText, a windowed control that displays text on a
  form. This component functions like TStaticText, but supports extended features such as hot tracking.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.AboutJVCL
  <INCLUDE JVCL.Main.AboutJVCL.dtx>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.Alignment
Summary
  Determines how text is aligned within the component.
Description
  The possible values of Alignment are

  <TABLE>
  Value            Meaning
  -----            ------- 
  taLeftJustify    Text is aligned at the left of the control.
  taCenter         Text is centered in the control.
  taRightJustify   Text is aligned at the right of the control.
  </TABLE>
See Also
  Layout
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.AutoSize
Summary
  Determines whether the component is automatically resized to accommodate its text.
Description
  If AutoSize is True, the component is automatically resized—at runtime and design time—whenever
  the font size or Caption text changes.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.BorderStyle
Summary
  Determines the appearance of the control’s border.
Description
  The possible values of BorderStyle are

  <TABLE>
  Value      Meaning
  -----      -------
  sbsNone    No visible border.
  sbsSingle  Single-line border.
  sbsSunken  Raised border.
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.FocusControl
Summary
  Links the component with another windowed control.
Description
  Use the FocusControl property to link the TJvCustomStaticText instance with another windowed control.
  If the text of Caption includes an accelerator key, the component specified by FocusControl receives
  focus when the accelerator is pressed.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.HintColor
Summary
  Determines the color of the hint boxes for the Help Hints for the <xxx>.
Description
  Use HintColor to specify the hint box color. A default color value of clInfoBk is set for the
  HintColor property in the constructor when the application is created. To change the HintColor
  assign it a new TColor value.
See Also
  HotTrack
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.HotTrack
Summary
  Specifies whether the control is highlighted when the mouse passes over it.
Description
  Set HotTrack to True to provide visual feedback about which item is under the mouse; the font
  specified by HotTrackFont is used for the control's text. When HotTrack is False, there is no visual
  feedback when the mouse passes over this control.
See Also
  OnMouseEnter, OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.HotTrackFont
Summary
  Specifies the font used when the mouse passes over the control, and HotTrack is True.
Description
  When the mouse passes over the control and HotTrack is set to True, HotTrackFont is used as the font
  for the control text.

  To change to a new font, specify a new TFont object. To modify a font, change the value of the
  Charset, Color, Height, Name, Pitch, Size, or Style of the TFont object.
See Also
  HotTrack
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.Layout
Summary
  Specifies the vertical placement of the text within the control.
Description
  Set Layout to specify how the text of the control is placed within the ClientRect of the control.
  Layout is the vertical analog to the Alignment property.

  Layout can be one of the following values:
  <TABLE>
  Value     Meaning
  -----     -------
  tlTop     The text appears at the top of the control. 
  tlCenter  The text is vertically centered in the control. 
  tlBottom  The text appears along the bottom of the control.
  </TABLE>
See Also
  Alignment
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.OnCtl3DChanged
Summary
  Occurs when the Ctl3D property of the control changes.
Description
  \Write an OnCtl3DChanged event handler to take specific action when the Ctl3D property changes.
See Also
  OnParentColorChange
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the control.
Description
  \Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse over the
  control.
See Also
  HotTrack, OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the control.
Description
  \Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse off the
  control. For example, you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an OnMouseEnter
  event handler.
See Also
  HotTrack, OnMouseEnter
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.OnParentColorChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color property for the parent of the control changes.
Description
  \Write an OnParentColorChange event to take specific action when the ParentColor property changes.
See Also
  OnCtl3DChanged
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.ShowAccelChar
Summary
  Enables accelerator characters.
Description
  If ShowAccelChar is True, an ampersand in the component’s Caption text appears as an underline and
  makes the character after it into an accelerator key. If ShowAccelChar is False, ampersands appear
  as ampersands.
See Also
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.TextMargins
Summary
  \Controls the indentation of the text on the control.
Description
  Use TextMargins to specify the indentation of the text on a control. 
See Also
  TJvTextMargins, TJvTextMargins.X, TJvTextMargins.Y
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomStaticText.WordWrap
Summary
  Specifies whether the control's text wraps when it is too long for the width of the control.
Description
  Set WordWrap to True to allow the control to display multiple line of text. When WordWrap is True,
  text that is too wide for the control wraps at the right margin and continues in additional
  lines.

  Set WordWrap to False to limit the control to a single line. When WordWrap is False, text that is too
  wide for the control appears truncated.
See Also
